        <h1>WIP Services</h1>
        <p>Users can now define a data service as a Work in Progress data service, which will help
        to prevent the service being a faulty service while if the service is under construction or
        any other reason.</p>
        <p>While creating the data service using the create wizard, you can click on 'Save as Draft'
        button to make the service as WIP service.</p>
        <p>
            <br/>
            <img src="images/user-guide/wip/wip_in_wizard.png"
                 alt="Create WIP Service"/>
            <br/>
            <br/>
        </p>
        <p>WIP service will be deployed and showed under deployed services list, yet it would not be
        an Active service. Therefore service will not be provide options to get the wsdls, and the
        try it options.</p>
         <p>
            <br/>
            <img src="images/user-guide/wip/wip_service_list.png"
                 alt="WIP Service in List"/>
            <br/>
            <br/>
        </p>

        <p>By click on 'Activate' link on the services dashboard or by finish the service
        after editing the data service you can make the service to an activate service.</p>
        <p>WIP Data Service file will be as follows.</p>
        <p>
            <br/>
            <img src="images/user-guide/wip/wip_dbs.png"
                 alt="WIP data service"/>
            <br/>
            <br/>
        </p>
